Coders Arcade â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â” DevOps Lab Manual
Â© 2025 Coders Arcade ğŸ“º www.youtube.com/c/codersarcade ğŸ‘¤ Saurav Sarkar
Locating elements by their id attribute and entering values:
Username: "standard_user"
Password: "secret_sauce"
sendKeys(value) â€“ Types the provided text into the input field.
ó¾ ³ Clicking the Login Button
Finds the login button using id="login-button" and clicks it.
Waits for 2 seconds to observe the login action.
ó¾ ´ Closing the Browser
Closes the browser after execution to free up system resources.
Summary of the Automation Process
âœ… Opens Google Chrome
âœ… Navigates to SauceDemo Login Page
âœ… Enters Username and Password
âœ… Clicks Login Button
âœ… Closes the browser
This simple example shows the power of Selenium for web automation, highlighting the disadvantages of manually
managing dependencies. This is why build tools like Maven & Gradle are needed, which we will explore after Version
Control Systems (Git & GitHub). ğŸš€
8. Problems with the Manual Approach
ğŸš© Time-Consuming â€“ Downloading and adding dependencies manually is inefficient.
ğŸš© Error-Prone â€“ Missing JAR files or incorrect configurations can break the project.
ğŸš© Difficult to Manage â€“ Dependencies are not automatically updated.
ğŸš© Not Scalable â€“ Every team member must manually configure their setup.
9. Why Do We Need Build Tools?
To overcome these inefficiencies, we use Maven & Gradle, which:
âœ… Automatically manage dependencies â€“ No need to download JARs manually. âœ… Simplify project configuration â€“ A single configuration file ( pom.xml for Maven, build.gradle.kts for Gradle)
handles everything.
âœ… Enable easy build & testing â€“ Run tests and package applications using simple commands.
âœ… Ensure consistency â€“ The same project setup works on different machines.
