3. Site Lifecycle
This lifecycle generates project documentation.
Phases:
pre-site â†’ Prepares documentation.
site â†’ Generates site documentation.
post-site â†’ Finalizes site generation.
site-deploy â†’ Deploys documentation to a web server.
Command to Run:
(This generates a project documentation site inside target/site .)
Summary Table:
Conclusion
Mavenâ€™s lifecycle ensures an automated, structured build process. Running any phase also executes all previous phases
automatically, making builds efficient and repeatable.
For daily use, the most common commands are:
